==English==
===Etymology===
Middle English ''menstruall,'' from Latin ''menstrualis,'' from ''menstrua'' [[menses]] (from neuter plural of ''menstruus'' of a month, monthly, of menstruation, from ''mensis'' month) + ''-alis'' -al -- more at [[moon|MOON]]
===Noun===
# of or having to do with the menses
# [Latin ''menstrualis,'' from ''menstruus'' + ''-alis'' -al] ''archaic''
#:a. occurring once a month : MONTHLY
#:b. lasting for a month 
#::a ''menstrual'' flower

